          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "The absence is real and it matters. But it does not define you. Grieve what you lost. Find mentors, spiritual fathers, or other men who can model what you did not receive. Most importantly, know that God offers what no absent earthly father can: constant, unconditional fatherhood. Your identity comes from God's truth about you, not from your father's presence or absence. You are not fatherless; you are invited into the family of God, where the Father of all never abandons."
